{% extends "layouts/standard_content.jinja" %}
{% from "components/card.jinja" import card %}
{% from "components/heading.jinja" import heading %}
{% from "components/contents.jinja" import contents %}
{% from "components/link.jinja" import link %}
{% from "components/list.jinja" import list, list_item %}
{% block mobile_article_title %}
  {% call heading() %}
    What you can do freely
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    Most uses of Find Case Law judgments don't require permission or a licence. You're free to use judgments under the Open Justice Licence in ways that support open justice, legal practice, research and commercial innovation.
  </p>
{% endblock mobile_article_title %}
{% block desktop_article_title %}
  {% call heading() %}
    What you can do freely
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    Most uses of Find Case Law judgments don't require permission or a licence. You're free to use judgments under the Open Justice Licence in ways that support open justice, legal practice, research and commercial innovation.
  </p>
{% endblock desktop_article_title %}
{% block article_navigation %}
  {% call contents(title="On this page") %}
    {% call list() %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#free-to-use") %}
          Free to use
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#commercial-use-is-permitted") %}
          Commercial use is permitted
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#what-you-cant-do-freely") %}
          What you can't do freely
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#full-terms") %}
          Full terms
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
      {% call list_item() %}
        {% call link(href="#questions-about-free-use") %}
          Questions about free use
        {% endcall %}
      {% endcall %}
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
{% endblock article_navigation %}
{% block article_content %}
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    Free to use
  {% endcall %}
  <p>Under the Open Justice Licence, you can freely:</p>
  {% call list(variant="bullets") %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      read and download any judgment from Find Case Law
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      share links to judgments with colleagues, clients, or the public
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      quote and cite judgments in your work, including academic papers, legal arguments, articles, and publications
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      use for legal research including case preparation, legal advice, and court submissions
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      teach and learn using judgments in educational settings
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      reference personally for your own understanding and study
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      use commercially including incorporating judgments into your own products or applications
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
  <p>No permission needed, no forms to fill in and no fees to pay.</p>
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    Commercial use is permitted
  {% endcall %}
  <p>The Open Justice Licence allows you to use judgments commercially. You can:</p>
  {% call list(variant="bullets") %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      copy, publish, distribute and transmit case law data
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      combine judgments with other information
    {% endcall %}
    {% call list_item() %}
      include judgments in your own product or application
    {% endcall %}
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    This means commercial legal technology products, legal databases and other commercial services can incorporate Find Case Law judgments freely.
  </p>
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    What you can't do freely
  {% endcall %}
  <p>The Open Justice Licence does not permit computational analysis.</p>
  <p>
    If you intend to do any programmatic searching in bulk across Find Case Law records to identify, extract or enrich contents within the records, you will need to apply for a licence to perform computational analysis.
  </p>
  <p>
    Visit
    {% call link(href=url("when_you_need_permission")) %}
      When you need permission
    {%- endcall -%}
    {{ " " }}to understand what counts as computational analysis.
  </p>
  {% call heading(tag="h2") %}
    Full terms
  {% endcall %}
  <p>
    {% call link(href=url("open_justice_licence")) %}
      Open Justice Licence
    {%- endcall -%}
    {{ " " }}provides the complete legal terms governing the use of Find Case Law judgments, including specific conditions and requirements.
  </p>
  {% call card(title="Questions about free use", title_tag="h2") %}
    <p>
      The Open Justice Licence covers the vast majority of how people want to use judgments, including commercial applications.
    </p>
    <p>
      Contact us at
      {% call link(href="mailto:caselawlicence@nationalarchives.gov.uk") %}
        caselawlicence@nationalarchives.gov.uk
      {%- endcall -%}
      {{ " " }}if you have specific questions about what the Open Justice Licence permits.
    </p>
  {% endcall %}
{% endblock article_content %}
